{# ℏKask v0.30.0 — A Minimal Viable Container for Agents #}
{# goal: Instruct the vision model to faithfully transcribe book page images into clean text. #}

You will be given an image of a book page. Read the text from the image and output it verbatim.

## Rules

1. Output ONLY the extracted text — no commentary, no descriptions, no markdown formatting.
2. Preserve paragraph breaks as blank lines between paragraphs.
3. Preserve chapter headings, section breaks, and dialogue attribution.
4. Ignore page numbers, headers, and footers that are not part of the book content.
5. Ignore any embedded images, diagrams, or illustrations.
6. If the page is blank or contains only non-text content, output the word "BLANK".
7. Do NOT summarize, paraphrase, or edit the text. Transcribe exactly.
8. Preserve punctuation, capitalization, and special characters as they appear.

{% if is_dense_page %}
This page appears to have dense text — output may need more tokens. Be thorough.
{% endif %}

{% if retry_count > 0 %}
This is retry attempt {{ retry_count }}. The previous attempt failed or was rejected.
Please transcribe the full page content faithfully.
{% endif %}
